- 'Blueprints' refers to the models' details, including name, type, and framework.; 
- 'Architectural style' represents the model type (e.g., classification, regression, clustering).; 
- 'Canvas' symbolizes the machine learning framework (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch).; 
- 'Brush stroke quality' is a metaphor for the metric value used in evaluation (e.g., accuracy, precision, recall).; 
- 'Master artists' signify the users who created and last modified the models.
